1. We click on the compiler button and it generates bytecode
2. then that bytecode is ran inside the JVM.
3. JRE contains your bytecode which can be run in JVM.
4. and JDK helps in conversion of high level code into bytcode.

so 2 commands runs when you click compilation buttion: Javac(generates bytcode), Java (runs bytecode inside JVM)

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

-target folder is automatically created by the compiler coz it contains your bytecodes. 
- the high level code cant be run in JVM. JVM always runs the bytecode.
